28/* Table for Big5 to UCS conversion. This is generated from the BIG5
29 charmap, using the following command:
30
31 egrep "/x../x.." BIG5 | egrep -v "^% " | sed 's/%IRREVERSIBLE%//' | \
32 perl segA.pl > segA
33
34 where segA.pl script is:
35
36 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
37print "static const uint16_t big5_to_ucs[13973] =\n{";
38while (<>) {
39 local($ucs, $big5, %rest) = split;
40 $ucs =~ s/<U(....)>/0x$1/;
41 $big5 =~ s/\/x//g;
42 $big5 = hex($big5) - 0xa140;
43 local($ridx) = int($big5 / 256) * 157;
44 if ($big5 % 256 > 0x3e) {
45 $ridx += ($big5 % 256) - 0x22;
46 } else {
47 $ridx += ($big5 % 256);
48 }
49 printf "\n " if (($n % 4) == 0);
50 ++$n;
51 printf " [%5d] = %s,", $ridx, $ucs;
52}
53print "\n};\n";
54
55~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
56*/

8377/* Definitions used in the body of the `gconv' function. */
8378#define CHARSET_NAME "BIG5//"
8379#define FROM_LOOP from_big5
8380#define TO_LOOP to_big5
8381#define DEFINE_INIT 1
8382#define DEFINE_FINI 1
8383#define MIN_NEEDED_FROM 1
8384#define MAX_NEEDED_FROM 2
8385#define MIN_NEEDED_TO 4
8386#define ONE_DIRECTION 0
8387
8388
8389/* First define the conversion function from Big5 to UCS4. */
8390#define MIN_NEEDED_INPUT MIN_NEEDED_FROM
8391#define MAX_NEEDED_INPUT MAX_NEEDED_FROM
8392#define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT MIN_NEEDED_TO
8393#define LOOPFCT FROM_LOOP
8394#define BODY \
8395 { \
8396 uint32_t ch = *inptr; \
8397 \
8398 if (ch >= 0xa1 && ch <= 0xf9) \
8399 { \
8400 /* Two-byte character. First test whether the next byte \
8401 is also available. */ \
8402 uint32_t ch2; \
8403 int idx; \
8404 \
8405 if (__glibc_unlikely (inptr + 1 >= inend)) \
8406 { \
8407 /* The second character is not available. */ \
8408 result = __GCONV_INCOMPLETE_INPUT; \
8409 break; \
8410 } \
8411 \
8412 idx = (ch - 0xa1) * 157; \
8413 ch2 = inptr[1]; \
8414 /* See whether the second byte is in the correct range. */ \
8415 if (ch2 >= 0x40 && ch2 <= 0x7e) \
8416 idx += ch2 - 0x40; \
8417 else if (__builtin_expect (ch2 >= 0xa1, 1) \
8418 && __builtin_expect (ch2 <= 0xfe, 1)) \
8419 idx += 0x3f + (ch2 - 0xa1); \
8420 else \
8421 { \
8422 /* This is illegal. */ \
8423 STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (1); \
8424 } \
8425 \
8426 /* Get the value from the table. */ \
8427 ch = big5_to_ucs[idx]; \
8428 \
8429 /* Is this character defined? */ \
8430 if (__glibc_unlikely (ch == 0)) \
8431 { \
8432 /* This is an illegal character. */ \
8433 STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (2); \
8434 } \
8435 \
8436 inptr += 2; \
8437 } \
8438 else if (ch <= 0x80) \
8439 ++inptr; \
8440 else \
8441 { \
8442 /* This is illegal. */ \
8443 STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (1); \
8444 } \
8445 \
8446 put32 (outptr, ch); \
8447 outptr += 4; \
8448 }
8449#define LOOP_NEED_FLAGS
8450#define ONEBYTE_BODY \
8451 { \
8452 if (c <= 0x80) \
8453 return c; \
8454 else \
8455 return WEOF; \
8456 }
8457#include <iconv/loop.c>

8462#define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT MIN_NEEDED_FROM
8463#define MAX_NEEDED_OUTPUT MAX_NEEDED_FROM
8464#define LOOPFCT TO_LOOP
8465#define BODY \
8466 { \
8467 uint32_t ch = get32 (inptr); \
8468 const char *cp; \
8469 \
8470 if (__builtin_expect (ch >= (sizeof (from_ucs4_tab1) \
8471 / sizeof (from_ucs4_tab1[0])), 0)) \
8472 switch (ch) \
8473 { \

8476 break; \

8479 break; \
8480 case 0x2013 ... 0x203b: \

8482 break; \

8500 break; \

8503 break; \
8504 case 0x2295: \

8551 /* Illegal character. */ \

8553 break; \
8554 } \
8555 else \

8557 \

8559 { \

8561 STANDARD_TO_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (4); \
8562 } \
8563 else \
8564 { \
8565 /* See whether there is enough room for the second byte we write. */ \
8566 if (__builtin_expect (cp[1], '\1') != '\0' \
8567 && __builtin_expect (outptr + 1 >= outend, 0)) \
8568 { \

8570 result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT; \
8571 break; \
8572 } \
8573 \
8574 *outptr++ = cp[0]; \
8575 if (cp[1] != '\0') \
8576 *outptr++ = cp[1]; \
8577 } \
8578 \
8579 inptr += 4; \
8580 }
